Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California Coast!

Name: Cachuma Lake
Description: Sleep under the stars in a tent and rent a boat during the day.

Name: Mission Santa Barbara
Description: Founded in 1786, current structure built in 1820.  It still holds church services today and also an archive library for education and research.

Name: Santa Barbara Botanic Garden
Description: 1,000 different plants, 5.5 miles of paths and a traditional Japanese Teahouse and Tea Garden for a mid-day pick-me-up.

Name: Santa Barbara County Courthouse Gardens
Description: Sign up for a free tour and picnic on the lawn afterwards.

Name: Isla Vista Food Cooperative
Description: Tiny grocery store offering fresh locally grown produce.
